1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:01,467
<i> I need to apologize.</i>

2
00:00:01,733 --> 00:00:04,200
<i> It's not her fault
</i>that I didn't have the courage.

3
00:00:04,333 --> 00:00:06,467
<i> Sorry, I'm late.</i>

4
00:00:06,600 --> 00:00:08,000
<i> May I have this dance?</i>

5
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:16,967
<i>- Are you resigning?
- Effective immediately.</i>

6
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:18,467
<i>Is this about the guest?
Because--</i>

7
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:20,233
It's about a lot of things, sir.

8
00:00:20,367 --> 00:00:23,833
<i>I'm not exactly required to
say why an employee is leaving.</i>

9
00:00:23,967 --> 00:00:25,167
<i> Ow! Let me go!</i>

10
00:00:25,300 --> 00:00:27,200
[GRUNTING]

11
00:00:27,333 --> 00:00:30,533
- [KICK LANDS]
- [BODY THUDS]

12
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,400
<i>- Come on.
- Hey.</i>

13
00:00:35,533 --> 00:00:37,133
<i> Hey, what's going on?</i>

14
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:43,300
[JUAN] Let me go!
You cowards!

15
00:00:43,433 --> 00:00:45,000
<i> Fight me fair and square!</i>

16
00:00:46,100 --> 00:00:49,600
I know you can hear me!
Let me out of here!

17
00:00:49,733 --> 00:00:52,567
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

18
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:54,200
Where's Sandro?

19
00:00:57,533 --> 00:01:00,567
Who are you?
What do you want with my dad?

20
00:01:02,767 --> 00:01:05,200
- Where is he?
- I don't know!

21
00:01:05,333 --> 00:01:11,533
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

22
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:14,400
Tell me the last thing
your father said to you.

23
00:01:14,533 --> 00:01:16,267
Why would I tell you?

24
00:01:18,133 --> 00:01:22,967
- [CRYING OUT IN PAIN]
- [GRUNTS LOUDLY, STOMPS]

25
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:26,333
If you want to keep breathing,
you'll talk!

26
00:01:26,467 --> 00:01:28,933
[COUGHING]

27
00:01:29,067 --> 00:01:31,267
[GRUNTING]

28
00:01:32,433 --> 00:01:39,200
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

29
00:02:42,167 --> 00:02:43,300
Mm.

30
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:50,100
["PANGHABANG IKAW"
BY DARREN ESPANTO PLAYING]

31
00:02:50,267 --> 00:02:51,267
Why?

32
00:02:52,367 --> 00:02:53,433
Is this awkward?

33
00:02:53,567 --> 00:02:58,000
["PANGHABANG IKAW" CONTINUES]

34
00:02:58,133 --> 00:03:02,567
Your cheeks aren't...
really chubby anymore, huh?

35
00:03:02,700 --> 00:03:04,200
[CHUCKLES]

36
00:03:05,100 --> 00:03:06,633
You missed them, didn't you?

37
00:03:07,467 --> 00:03:10,467
Mm... Now I do.

38
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:12,233
Eddybear.

39
00:03:13,900 --> 00:03:15,067
- [GIGGLES]
- [CHUCKLES]

40
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:17,733
I haven't heard that
in a long time.

41
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:23,600
You know,
if I'd known back then...

42
00:03:23,733 --> 00:03:27,033
I would've made the most
of pinching your cheeks

43
00:03:27,167 --> 00:03:30,300
and called you Eddybear
every single day.

44
00:03:31,433 --> 00:03:34,367
- Really? Huh?
- Hmm!

45
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:35,767
Well, I mean...

46
00:03:37,433 --> 00:03:40,333
You were embarrassed by
me in front of your classmates.

47
00:03:42,333 --> 00:03:45,100
You only came to see me
when they weren't around.

48
00:03:48,567 --> 00:03:49,700
Right?

49
00:03:49,833 --> 00:03:54,033
["PANGHABANG IKAW" CONTINUES]

50
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:55,233
Ed--

51
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,300
What are you doing?

52
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:02,567
Just checking if I'm dreaming.

53
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:04,433
[GIGGLES]

54
00:04:04,567 --> 00:04:07,100
I still can't believe that...

55
00:04:07,233 --> 00:04:09,733
you said yes to being
my prom date back then.

56
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:14,700
You know...

57
00:04:16,333 --> 00:04:18,400
I really wanted to go.

58
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:23,167
Something just happened.

59
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:30,500
My mom and dad...
they were fighting then.

60
00:04:30,667 --> 00:04:32,900
I thought they were
going to split up.

61
00:04:33,033 --> 00:04:37,733
I fell apart back then.

62
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:39,933
I'm sorry.

63
00:04:42,967 --> 00:04:45,933
I wish you had just told me
the truth back then.

64
00:04:50,067 --> 00:04:52,267
Did you think
I wouldn't understand?

65
00:04:55,433 --> 00:04:56,733
I'm sorry.

66
00:04:58,133 --> 00:05:00,133
I'm sorry I didn't show up.

67
00:05:03,567 --> 00:05:05,967
I'm sorry it took me
this long to say sorry.

68
00:05:07,700 --> 00:05:10,167
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay, Jade.

69
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:14,100
I already forgave you.

70
00:05:15,867 --> 00:05:17,067
That was fast.

71
00:05:18,733 --> 00:05:19,800
[EDWARD] There.

72
00:05:19,933 --> 00:05:23,933
You should always be
like that. Okay?

73
00:05:24,067 --> 00:05:26,367
A smile really suits you.

74
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:28,533
Just like that, smile. Okay?

75
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:32,400
Edward, thank you.

76
00:05:32,533 --> 00:05:33,900
Thank you for tonight.

77
00:05:34,967 --> 00:05:37,133
I really appreciate this.

78
00:05:39,067 --> 00:05:41,967
Eddybear.
[CHUCKLES]

79
00:05:42,100 --> 00:05:43,800
Oh, so you're really
not going to stop

80
00:05:43,933 --> 00:05:45,067
with the "Eddybear," huh?

81
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:48,067
Why? Am I not allowed
to call you Eddybear anymore?

82
00:05:48,867 --> 00:05:50,000
Fine.

83
00:05:50,133 --> 00:05:53,867
If that's what's going
to keep you happy,

84
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:58,567
I'll change my name
on my birth certificate.

85
00:05:58,700 --> 00:06:00,100
For real?

86
00:06:00,233 --> 00:06:02,600
- Eddybear Arellano.
- [BOTH LAUGHING]

87
00:06:02,733 --> 00:06:04,300
At your service.

88
00:06:05,833 --> 00:06:09,767
[BOTH LAUGHING]

89
00:06:09,933 --> 00:06:13,533
[ENGINE REVVING]

90
00:06:15,533 --> 00:06:16,733
[HANDBRAKE ENGAGING]

91
00:06:16,867 --> 00:06:18,367
[ENGINE POWERING DOWN]

92
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:19,600
[CAR DOORS OPEN]

93
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:23,267
[CAR DOORS CLOSE]

94
00:06:24,233 --> 00:06:26,367
[JUSTIN] What were you
thinking, huh?!

95
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:27,600
I'm sorry.

96
00:06:27,733 --> 00:06:30,033
We didn't know a kidnapping
was going to happen--

97
00:06:30,167 --> 00:06:33,233
You think I knew
that would happen? Huh?

98
00:06:33,367 --> 00:06:35,533
My point is, why
did you have to follow me?!

99
00:06:35,667 --> 00:06:38,267
Trixie just wanted to
talk to you... Just calm down--

100
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:40,400
Is this about the bar?!
[SCOFFS]

101
00:06:40,533 --> 00:06:42,167
Fine! Okay!

102
00:06:42,333 --> 00:06:44,133
You're acting like this
because of that?!

103
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:47,967
I'll make sure the bar gets
handed over to you, alright?!

104
00:06:48,100 --> 00:06:49,767
Are you happy now?
Is that enough?!

105
00:06:49,900 --> 00:06:51,433
Justin...

106
00:06:51,567 --> 00:06:52,900
I'm sorry. Stop being angry.

107
00:06:53,033 --> 00:06:54,300
It's over, it already happened.

108
00:06:54,433 --> 00:06:56,600
[JUSTIN] You think it's just
that easy? It already happened?

109
00:06:56,733 --> 00:06:58,000
We almost died.

110
00:06:58,133 --> 00:06:59,900
Your lives were put at risk
because of me.

111
00:07:00,033 --> 00:07:01,900
What if something bad
happened to you?

112
00:07:02,033 --> 00:07:03,200
Then I'd be the villain again,
right?

113
00:07:03,333 --> 00:07:05,200
So, what do you want us to do?

114
00:07:05,333 --> 00:07:07,900
You want me to rewind time so
you won't be mad anymore?

115
00:07:08,033 --> 00:07:10,433
I said it's over. It happened.

116
00:07:10,567 --> 00:07:11,700
You seem even angrier now.

117
00:07:11,833 --> 00:07:14,267
We've been trying
to talk to you calmly,

118
00:07:14,433 --> 00:07:16,500
but you keep raising your voice.
You keep screaming.

119
00:07:16,633 --> 00:07:17,800
Of course I'm screaming,

120
00:07:17,933 --> 00:07:20,100
so you'll understand that your
lives are in danger right now!

121
00:07:20,233 --> 00:07:22,900
We already know that!
Stop screaming!

122
00:07:23,033 --> 00:07:24,367
I'll scream if I want to!

123
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:25,633
Fine, let's go then.

124
00:07:25,767 --> 00:07:26,933
- Let's see who can yell louder!
- I'll scream if I want to!

125
00:07:27,067 --> 00:07:28,967
- You're being stubborn!
- Fine! You aren't listening!

126
00:07:29,100 --> 00:07:30,267
- You're getting on my nerves!
- You're not listening!

127
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:32,033
- Go ahead, louder!
- Fine, I'll go louder!

128
00:07:32,167 --> 00:07:33,333
- Please, stop shouting!
- You're not listening!

129
00:07:33,467 --> 00:07:35,933
Stop shouting!
Stop shouting, please!

130
00:07:36,833 --> 00:07:40,667
[TRIXIE SOBS]

131
00:07:41,967 --> 00:07:43,767
Oh my god...

132
00:07:43,900 --> 00:07:46,767
I'm sorry, I'm sorry,
I'm sorry...

133
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:48,900
- Stop crying, it's okay.
- [COUGHS]

134
00:07:49,067 --> 00:07:51,267
I'm sorry. Please stop crying.

135
00:07:54,667 --> 00:07:56,000
[TRIXIE] Justin...

136
00:07:58,033 --> 00:07:59,433
I'm sorry.

137
00:08:00,933 --> 00:08:02,633
I'm really, really sorry.

138
00:08:03,533 --> 00:08:05,233
I promise, I mean it.

139
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:08,133
I just wanted
to apologize right away

140
00:08:08,267 --> 00:08:10,967
because I realized...
an apology

141
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:13,533
is for the person who
was hurt, not for me, Justin.

142
00:08:13,667 --> 00:08:15,133
I'm sorry, I was wrong.

143
00:08:16,167 --> 00:08:19,500
That's why I forced Cheska
to follow you.

144
00:08:21,467 --> 00:08:23,867
I'm really sorry, Justin,
for everything I said.

145
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:26,600
I... I did not mean any of that.

146
00:08:26,733 --> 00:08:28,300
You don't deserve that.

147
00:08:29,333 --> 00:08:31,800
And I'm sorry
for ruining your plan.

148
00:08:31,933 --> 00:08:33,200
I'm sorry.

149
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:41,267
- [SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]
- [TRIXIE SOBS SOFTLY]

150
00:08:47,933 --> 00:08:50,467
So? Are we okay?

151
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:56,300
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

152
00:08:56,467 --> 00:08:58,333
Who were those guys anyway?

153
00:09:00,633 --> 00:09:02,100
I don't even know them.

154
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:07,700
But... the one who got
taken, you know him, right?

155
00:09:07,833 --> 00:09:09,567
Who is he? Your friend?

156
00:09:09,700 --> 00:09:12,700
What is he to you? Why
did you just let them take him?

157
00:09:13,867 --> 00:09:16,400
Hey, Justin...

158
00:09:16,533 --> 00:09:18,267
Tell us.

159
00:09:20,133 --> 00:09:23,133
We're already involved anyway.
Just say it.

160
00:09:23,267 --> 00:09:28,200
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

161
00:09:28,367 --> 00:09:30,033
Come on, Justin.
[SNIFFLES]

162
00:09:30,167 --> 00:09:33,533
It's too late now.
We're in this together. Tell us.

163
00:09:33,667 --> 00:09:38,767
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

164
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:41,633
It started when I noticed...

165
00:09:41,767 --> 00:09:43,533
Leon was hiding
something from us.

166
00:09:46,133 --> 00:09:47,900
I kept an eye on him

167
00:09:49,133 --> 00:09:51,067
until I found out for sure
he was lying

168
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,667
about where he was going.

169
00:09:54,467 --> 00:09:56,300
What if he's just
on a secret date?

170
00:09:57,533 --> 00:10:00,067
Then why does he have a profile
of Juan's missing father?

171
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:04,533
When I confronted him about
it, he went totally silent.

172
00:10:04,667 --> 00:10:06,067
Isn't that suspicious?

173
00:10:07,733 --> 00:10:09,633
Well, he's still your brother,
Justin.

174
00:10:09,767 --> 00:10:12,500
- I think you should trust him.
- [SCOFFS]

175
00:10:12,633 --> 00:10:13,767
I can't just sit here
and do nothing

176
00:10:13,900 --> 00:10:16,833
while Juan is clearly
targeting Leon.

177
00:10:18,167 --> 00:10:22,300
What if Kiko or Martin
were in danger?

178
00:10:22,433 --> 00:10:24,033
Would you guys
just let that happen?

179
00:10:24,167 --> 00:10:25,900
- No.
- No way.

180
00:10:26,033 --> 00:10:27,033
Not me.

181
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:32,367
Look, I'm not doing this to make
Leon look like the bad guy.

182
00:10:32,500 --> 00:10:35,067
Yeah, I've screwed up
a lot in the past.

183
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:38,533
But I'm keeping my promise,
now that Dad's gone,

184
00:10:38,667 --> 00:10:40,967
I'm supposed to be
the one protecting our family.

185
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:44,700
I'm doing this for Leon,
but for Luna and Jade, too.

186
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:49,733
Don't worry.

187
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:53,300
I'll help you find the answers
you're looking for.

188
00:10:53,433 --> 00:10:55,700
What? No!

189
00:10:56,933 --> 00:10:58,667
You told me
to just say what I knew, right?

190
00:11:01,667 --> 00:11:02,900
Justin...

191
00:11:04,100 --> 00:11:05,567
What do you want?

192
00:11:05,700 --> 00:11:07,300
Do you want our help,

193
00:11:07,433 --> 00:11:10,000
or do you want us following
you without you knowing?

194
00:11:11,567 --> 00:11:12,933
Me too.

195
00:11:13,067 --> 00:11:14,267
I will help.

196
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:16,933
We will help.

197
00:11:19,867 --> 00:11:22,633
Justin, let us
help you.

198
00:11:22,767 --> 00:11:24,267
It's just us now.

199
00:11:25,433 --> 00:11:27,100
We're already involved.

200
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:31,833
Besides, isn't it better?
There are three of us.

201
00:11:31,967 --> 00:11:34,700
We've got
each other's backs, right?

202
00:11:34,833 --> 00:11:36,667
But I have a suggestion.

203
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:41,233
Whatever we know,
whatever we've seen,

204
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:42,967
we need to tell the police.

205
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,067
Deal?

206
00:11:46,267 --> 00:11:47,400
Deal.

207
00:11:48,567 --> 00:11:49,867
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

208
00:11:52,300 --> 00:11:53,867
[HUSHING]

209
00:11:57,633 --> 00:12:00,100
[MECHANICAL WHIRRING]

210
00:12:02,267 --> 00:12:03,800
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

211
00:12:07,733 --> 00:12:10,800
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

212
00:12:10,933 --> 00:12:13,767
[LEON] This is clearly
Uncle Andy and Sandro.

213
00:12:17,633 --> 00:12:20,067
Why did he lie and
say he didn't know them?

214
00:12:23,267 --> 00:12:25,867
Is he hiding something
from our family?

215
00:12:30,433 --> 00:12:34,467
[PENSIVE MUSIC BUILDS]

216
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:40,733
- [WHISTLING]
- [WATER RUNNING]

217
00:12:40,867 --> 00:12:42,400
[DOOR OPENS]

218
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:45,100
I'm back.

219
00:12:45,233 --> 00:12:46,733
[DOOR CLOSES]

220
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:48,733
- Dad.
- Hey.

221
00:12:48,900 --> 00:12:50,300
Aren't you going
to get some rest?

222
00:12:50,433 --> 00:12:53,433
Um, yeah. In a while.
I'll go lay down soon.

223
00:12:53,567 --> 00:12:54,800
Okay.

224
00:12:54,933 --> 00:12:57,367
Oh, you look happy.
I take it the date went well?

225
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:58,400
[CHUCKLES]

226
00:12:58,533 --> 00:12:59,767
Yes, Dad.

227
00:13:00,567 --> 00:13:02,533
We had a wonderful time.

228
00:13:02,667 --> 00:13:03,800
Good, good.

229
00:13:03,933 --> 00:13:05,967
Based on her reaction
the last time she was here,

230
00:13:06,100 --> 00:13:07,567
I thought she'd be angry.

231
00:13:07,700 --> 00:13:09,433
Ah. No, no, no.

232
00:13:09,567 --> 00:13:10,967
We talked it out.

233
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:16,133
And... things
are actually better this time.

234
00:13:16,267 --> 00:13:17,433
[CHUCKLES]

235
00:13:17,567 --> 00:13:18,600
Okay.

236
00:13:18,733 --> 00:13:20,167
I hope you two
aren't up to anything crazy.

237
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:22,967
Dad... there you go again.
Come on.

238
00:13:24,167 --> 00:13:26,633
Look, I won't pry
into your privacy.

239
00:13:26,767 --> 00:13:27,900
- I'm happy...
- Right.

240
00:13:28,033 --> 00:13:30,133
...as long as
you guys are doing okay.

241
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:33,300
And that just means
nothing can stop my plans now.

242
00:13:33,433 --> 00:13:35,400
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

243
00:13:35,533 --> 00:13:36,900
Plans?

244
00:13:38,033 --> 00:13:40,267
What plans?
Plans for what?

245
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:43,833
Plans for... for Hotel 88.

246
00:13:43,967 --> 00:13:46,267
You know,
with us being partners.

247
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:49,600
And, uh... doing what we can
to help Jade and the others.

248
00:13:49,733 --> 00:13:51,967
Oh, okay.
Y-Yeah, of course.

249
00:13:52,100 --> 00:13:53,667
Alright.
Good night, bud.

250
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:54,867
Good night, Dad.

251
00:13:55,033 --> 00:14:02,033
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

252
00:14:05,133 --> 00:14:06,967
[JUSTIN] I'll be the one
to talk to the police, okay?

253
00:14:07,100 --> 00:14:09,133
Only speak
when you're spoken to.

254
00:14:09,267 --> 00:14:11,500
Look at you.
You act like you know exactly

255
00:14:11,633 --> 00:14:13,133
how things work on the inside.

256
00:14:13,267 --> 00:14:15,533
It sounds bad, but
I'm a regular at the precinct.

257
00:14:15,667 --> 00:14:17,567
What? How many offenses
do you have

258
00:14:17,700 --> 00:14:18,767
to have to call yourself
a "regular"?

259
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:20,700
Hey, it's not all me.

260
00:14:20,833 --> 00:14:23,267
Sometimes I'm just there
to bail out my friends.

261
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:24,900
And you're proud of that?

262
00:14:26,233 --> 00:14:28,400
What story did you give your
siblings for leaving the hotel?

263
00:14:28,567 --> 00:14:31,167
I said I was handling things
at Trixie's new bar.

264
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,800
- Wait.
- [JUSTIN] What?

265
00:14:33,933 --> 00:14:35,967
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

266
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:38,300
- Let's go this way!
- Are we hiding again?

267
00:14:38,433 --> 00:14:44,000
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

268
00:14:46,667 --> 00:14:50,033
What's going on?

269
00:14:50,167 --> 00:14:51,667
[TRIXIE] Look.
That's him, right?

270
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:53,433
That's the guy who took Juan?

271
00:14:53,567 --> 00:14:56,533
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

272
00:14:56,667 --> 00:14:58,900
Oh my god,
what if he recognized me?

273
00:15:03,433 --> 00:15:05,633
You still remember it, Trixie?

274
00:15:05,767 --> 00:15:07,833
That's trauma for me, Cheska.

275
00:15:07,967 --> 00:15:09,033
[BREATHING SHARPLY]

276
00:15:09,167 --> 00:15:10,433
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

277
00:15:10,567 --> 00:15:13,633
So now what? They seem
to be getting along,

278
00:15:13,767 --> 00:15:16,633
even laughing together.

279
00:15:16,767 --> 00:15:20,100
If he's got an accomplice
inside, we can't file a report.

280
00:15:20,233 --> 00:15:21,300
It's too risky for us.

281
00:15:21,433 --> 00:15:24,533
[HEAVY FOOTSTEPS IN DISTANCE]

282
00:15:24,667 --> 00:15:25,733
Hey, let's get out of here.

283
00:15:25,867 --> 00:15:27,333
We can't let them see us.
Let's go.

284
00:15:27,467 --> 00:15:29,933
- Come on, come on.
- Hurry up.

285
00:15:30,067 --> 00:15:34,500
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

286
00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:36,067
[WAVES LAPPING]

287
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:39,633
[GIO]<i> Did you ghost me
</i> because of that guy?

288
00:15:39,767 --> 00:15:42,867
<i>Did Peter make you not want
to talk about the past?</i>

289
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,033
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

290
00:15:44,167 --> 00:15:47,167
<i>Because you're fine
with forgetting our history.</i>

291
00:15:47,300 --> 00:15:52,033
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

292
00:15:52,167 --> 00:15:53,433
[KIKO] Have you just arrived?

293
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:56,100
[GIO] Mm-hmm.

294
00:15:57,233 --> 00:15:58,133
[RAPHIE] Gentlemen!

295
00:15:58,733 --> 00:16:00,100
Hello!

296
00:16:00,233 --> 00:16:01,800
Oh, Sir Gio!

297
00:16:01,933 --> 00:16:03,167
Welcome back!

298
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:09,733
Raphie, is Jade still not here?

299
00:16:09,900 --> 00:16:11,600
Uh... Not yet.

300
00:16:11,733 --> 00:16:14,433
I haven't spotted her
at the front desk.

301
00:16:14,567 --> 00:16:15,500
[KIKO SIGHS]

302
00:16:15,633 --> 00:16:18,333
She's not replying
to my texts.

303
00:16:18,467 --> 00:16:20,033
I'm getting worried.

304
00:16:20,167 --> 00:16:23,400
[RAPHIE] Oh, she might
show up with Miss Luna.

305
00:16:23,533 --> 00:16:25,500
[KIKO] But she's not coming
to work today.

306
00:16:25,633 --> 00:16:27,800
At least that's what Martin
said earlier.

307
00:16:27,933 --> 00:16:30,167
Leon already sent him
a message about it.

308
00:16:30,300 --> 00:16:32,400
So I'm really just
waiting for Jade.

309
00:16:32,533 --> 00:16:34,433
[RAPHIE] Ah, is that so?

310
00:16:34,567 --> 00:16:37,267
I guess I won't be feeling
Luna's energy today.

311
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:38,500
[KIKO] Sadly, nope.

312
00:16:38,633 --> 00:16:40,467
And she doesn't have
any energy at all.

313
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:43,000
Leon said she's sick.

314
00:16:43,167 --> 00:16:48,200
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

315
00:16:48,333 --> 00:16:49,633
[JADE]
Luna, take your medicine.

316
00:16:49,767 --> 00:16:51,333
[LEON]
I've been in touch with Martin.

317
00:16:51,467 --> 00:16:53,067
- [LUNA] Thank you.
- Get some rest today.

318
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:54,033
[PILLS RATTLING]

319
00:16:54,167 --> 00:16:55,000
He's right, Luna.

320
00:16:55,133 --> 00:16:59,467
You might get sick
from all that stress.

321
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:01,033
[LEON] Stress?

322
00:17:01,167 --> 00:17:02,167
Why?

323
00:17:02,300 --> 00:17:03,367
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

324
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:05,233
Oh no, it's nothing, Leon.

325
00:17:05,367 --> 00:17:07,500
It's just
about the bank notice.

326
00:17:09,067 --> 00:17:11,800
Jade, aren't you going
to the hotel?

327
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:14,533
I was thinking of taking
a half day off,

328
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:17,233
if that's okay,
so I can tend to Luna.

329
00:17:17,367 --> 00:17:18,200
[LEON] Go to work now.

330
00:17:18,333 --> 00:17:19,967
You're needed there,

331
00:17:20,100 --> 00:17:22,733
especially since Luna and I
can't be present.

332
00:17:22,867 --> 00:17:23,967
Come on.

333
00:17:24,100 --> 00:17:25,767
[JADE]
Luna, sit down on the bed.

334
00:17:25,900 --> 00:17:27,500
- Thank you.
- Message me anytime.

335
00:17:27,633 --> 00:17:30,167
- Whatever you need.
- Yes. Thank you, Jade.

336
00:17:30,300 --> 00:17:32,067
- Take it slowly.
- Be careful.

337
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:33,167
Okay.

338
00:17:33,300 --> 00:17:34,233
- You'll be okay here?
- Mmm.

339
00:17:34,367 --> 00:17:35,267
Leon.

340
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:42,267
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

341
00:17:46,433 --> 00:17:48,067
Leon, do you have
anything to say?

342
00:17:49,100 --> 00:17:51,167
I don't think now is
the right time.

343
00:17:51,300 --> 00:17:52,767
Rest up.

344
00:17:53,633 --> 00:17:54,933
I'll just get sicker

345
00:17:55,067 --> 00:17:58,533
if I have to keep thinking
about what you'll say.

346
00:17:58,667 --> 00:18:03,567
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

347
00:18:03,700 --> 00:18:05,633
It's about Uncle Andy.

348
00:18:05,767 --> 00:18:07,600
What about Uncle Andy?

349
00:18:08,767 --> 00:18:11,867
I'm no longer sure if I want
him to be a hotel partner.

350
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:14,267
Why? Is it-- Is it the terms?

351
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:15,933
You don't agree anymore?

352
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:20,000
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

353
00:18:20,133 --> 00:18:21,067
It's not that.

354
00:18:22,100 --> 00:18:23,133
Then what?

355
00:18:25,067 --> 00:18:27,233
Don't you think there will be
a conflict of interest?

356
00:18:27,367 --> 00:18:29,467
I mean, they also have a hotel.

357
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:30,967
It might affect ours.

358
00:18:31,100 --> 00:18:32,700
[LUNA] Wouldn't that be better?

359
00:18:32,833 --> 00:18:34,400
Uncle Andy can teach us
everything he knows

360
00:18:34,533 --> 00:18:36,467
about the hotel business.

361
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:39,000
I'm just not sure
what his intentions are.

362
00:18:39,133 --> 00:18:42,033
Sure, he had been friends with
Dad for a long time, but...

363
00:18:42,167 --> 00:18:44,100
they never did
business together.

364
00:18:44,233 --> 00:18:46,733
[LUNA] We didn't have a
hotel before, Leon.

365
00:18:46,867 --> 00:18:49,900
Not to mention, Dad was focused
on his existing businesses.

366
00:18:50,033 --> 00:18:51,633
I just think it's better
if we lock in

367
00:18:51,767 --> 00:18:53,933
the partner Martin's getting.

368
00:18:54,067 --> 00:18:57,167
Hang on, we already settled on
securing two business partners.

369
00:18:57,333 --> 00:18:59,767
[LUNA] The more money
that comes in, the better.

370
00:18:59,900 --> 00:19:02,133
Besides, the papers are
already sorted out.

371
00:19:02,267 --> 00:19:04,633
[SIGHING DEEPLY]

372
00:19:05,533 --> 00:19:07,233
I have a bad feeling about this.

373
00:19:07,367 --> 00:19:08,967
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

374
00:19:09,100 --> 00:19:12,933
And what I feel is that Uncle
Andy is the right partner.

375
00:19:13,067 --> 00:19:15,333
We need him.

376
00:19:15,467 --> 00:19:17,133
We will bring him in.

377
00:19:26,867 --> 00:19:28,567
Not one impressed you?

378
00:19:28,967 --> 00:19:30,533
Sir, this is the second batch
of applicants,

379
00:19:30,667 --> 00:19:32,333
and still no one passed.

380
00:19:32,633 --> 00:19:34,233
Do you want
to meet them yourself?

381
00:19:34,367 --> 00:19:35,200
No need.

382
00:19:35,333 --> 00:19:37,200
Their resumés don't even
make the cut.

383
00:19:38,467 --> 00:19:40,833
One didn't last long
at their previous job.

384
00:19:40,967 --> 00:19:42,967
Another wants flexible hours.

385
00:19:43,100 --> 00:19:46,100
Another lives in the next town,
so of course they'll be late.

386
00:19:46,233 --> 00:19:49,100
What if we tell them
to move here?

387
00:19:49,233 --> 00:19:50,433
Lateness won't be
a problem then.

388
00:19:50,567 --> 00:19:52,300
No, because this person
is a working student.

389
00:19:52,433 --> 00:19:54,367
They must be fully dedicated.

390
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:57,433
[WHISPERING]
He wanted a dedicated person?

391
00:19:57,567 --> 00:19:59,867
Then why did he let go of Sari?

392
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:00,900
What was that, Raphie?

393
00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:02,500
Ah, no, sir.
What I mean is...

394
00:20:02,667 --> 00:20:04,900
If none of the applicants
impressed you,

395
00:20:05,033 --> 00:20:06,867
maybe you should get
someone back.

396
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:08,133
No.

397
00:20:08,267 --> 00:20:10,433
Want me to help convince Sari
to come back?

398
00:20:10,567 --> 00:20:13,533
That's better than hiring
someone new.

399
00:20:13,667 --> 00:20:17,233
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

400
00:20:17,567 --> 00:20:19,133
Get me new applicants.

401
00:20:19,267 --> 00:20:21,700
Or else, you will
be my assistant.

402
00:20:21,833 --> 00:20:22,833
[TAPPING SHOULDER]

403
00:20:24,867 --> 00:20:26,100
No, no, no, no.

404
00:20:26,233 --> 00:20:28,200
I want a peaceful life!

405
00:20:28,333 --> 00:20:30,333
Sari! Girl, where are you?!

406
00:20:30,467 --> 00:20:31,600
- [BROOM STICK RUSTLING]
- [SNEEZES]

407
00:20:31,733 --> 00:20:32,633
Hey, thirteen!

408
00:20:32,767 --> 00:20:33,533
[SARI COUGHING]

409
00:20:33,667 --> 00:20:34,900
Looks like someone
thought of you.

410
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:36,367
Letter M.

411
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:37,633
You just crossed his mind.

412
00:20:37,767 --> 00:20:39,600
His name starts
with the letter M.

413
00:20:39,733 --> 00:20:40,633
"M"?

414
00:20:40,767 --> 00:20:41,967
Mar... [GASPS]

415
00:20:42,100 --> 00:20:43,500
M-Mama!

416
00:20:43,633 --> 00:20:45,267
Mama misses me up there
in heaven.

417
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,367
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

418
00:20:46,500 --> 00:20:47,967
Mama, please!

419
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:51,767
Please help me find a new job.

420
00:20:51,900 --> 00:20:53,333
Give me a sign.

421
00:20:53,467 --> 00:20:56,067
Oh? I thought the signs
were wrong.

422
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:59,300
They only made a mistake
with Sir Martin.

423
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:04,300
Well, should we just burn this?

424
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:05,667
Grandpa!

425
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:08,067
You entered
the wrong job, anyway.

426
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:10,033
- Don't, Grandpa.
- Why?

427
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:11,300
- Please, no.
- But why?

428
00:21:11,433 --> 00:21:13,167
It would be a waste.

429
00:21:13,300 --> 00:21:15,800
This can--
This can still be useful.

430
00:21:15,933 --> 00:21:17,600
It's still good.

431
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:19,233
Still good?

432
00:21:19,367 --> 00:21:20,800
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

433
00:21:20,933 --> 00:21:22,633
- Is that right?
- It's still good, Grandpa.

434
00:21:22,767 --> 00:21:25,433
Okay. You said it yourself.

435
00:21:25,567 --> 00:21:26,900
It's still good.

436
00:21:29,367 --> 00:21:30,533
Mmm.

437
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:41,567
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

438
00:21:42,467 --> 00:21:44,533
Really, Uncle?
You're going to invest in us?

439
00:21:44,667 --> 00:21:45,700
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

440
00:21:45,833 --> 00:21:47,000
Ah, yes.

441
00:21:47,133 --> 00:21:49,167
We'll discuss this over lunch
the day after tomorrow.

442
00:21:49,300 --> 00:21:50,433
Of course, Uncle.

443
00:21:50,567 --> 00:21:52,433
I'll arrange our lunch
meeting myself.

444
00:21:52,567 --> 00:21:55,100
Mmm. Oh, and don't forget
to bring Sari, okay?

445
00:21:56,433 --> 00:21:57,800
S-Sari?

446
00:21:57,933 --> 00:22:00,600
[RONALD]<i> Ah, yes.
</i> I told Carmela about her.

447
00:22:00,733 --> 00:22:04,000
And, uh, she wants
to meet Sari.

448
00:22:04,667 --> 00:22:07,133
Uh, Uncle, about that...

449
00:22:07,267 --> 00:22:10,567
I don't know
about Sari's schedule.

450
00:22:10,700 --> 00:22:13,867
But the three of us can meet.

451
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:14,933
[SIGHS]

452
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:16,467
Sari won't be there?

453
00:22:17,300 --> 00:22:19,433
<i>Your Aunt Carmela was looking
forward to seeing her.</i>

454
00:22:19,567 --> 00:22:21,233
<i> But more importantly,</i>

455
00:22:21,367 --> 00:22:23,933
what she told me about you

456
00:22:24,067 --> 00:22:27,800
is one of the reasons I agreed
to this partnership.

457
00:22:28,533 --> 00:22:30,567
I-I understand, but...

458
00:22:30,700 --> 00:22:33,500
<i> Well, we can reschedule.</i>

459
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:35,400
Oh! No, no, no.

460
00:22:35,533 --> 00:22:37,167
Let's proceed with this, Uncle.

461
00:22:37,300 --> 00:22:39,200
I just remembered that, uh...

462
00:22:39,333 --> 00:22:43,400
Yes, Sari's free the day
after tomorrow.

463
00:22:43,533 --> 00:22:46,867
Okay. Good.
I'll see you then.

464
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:48,033
See you, too.

465
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:51,600
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

466
00:22:52,333 --> 00:22:53,300
Nope.

467
00:22:53,433 --> 00:22:54,400
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

468
00:22:54,533 --> 00:22:55,900
No, I won't call her.

469
00:22:56,567 --> 00:22:58,100
I can't, I can't, I can't.

470
00:23:03,533 --> 00:23:04,733
For the hotel.

471
00:23:06,300 --> 00:23:07,433
Nope!

472
00:23:08,100 --> 00:23:09,400
She's the one who quit!

473
00:23:09,533 --> 00:23:10,567
It's her life, anyway!

474
00:23:10,700 --> 00:23:13,400
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

475
00:23:13,533 --> 00:23:14,633
[SIGHS]

476
00:23:16,967 --> 00:23:17,767
[LINE RINGING]

477
00:23:17,900 --> 00:23:19,000
[BUSY TONE]

478
00:23:19,133 --> 00:23:20,133
What the--?

479
00:23:21,300 --> 00:23:22,633
[CLICKS TONGUE, SIGHS]

480
00:23:24,433 --> 00:23:25,467
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

481
00:23:25,600 --> 00:23:27,100
[MARTIN] Sari, let's talk.

482
00:23:35,500 --> 00:23:38,200
[BIRDS TRILLING, CHIRPING]

483
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:40,200
[RAPHIE] One hot Americano.

484
00:23:40,333 --> 00:23:42,667
- Thank you.
- My pleasure, sir.

485
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:44,767
Is there anything else
I can help you with?

486
00:23:45,533 --> 00:23:46,800
Uh, not really.

487
00:23:46,933 --> 00:23:49,933
I would like to stay
at Hotel 88.

488
00:23:50,067 --> 00:23:52,133
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

489
00:23:52,267 --> 00:23:53,233
Thank you, sir.

490
00:23:57,367 --> 00:23:58,833
What are you doing here?

491
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:14,500
<i> Do you have a girlfriend?</i>

492
00:24:15,233 --> 00:24:17,067
<i> Nope. Super single.</i>

493
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:18,333
<i>- Good morning.
- Hello.</i>

494
00:24:18,467 --> 00:24:20,933
<i>We're Sari's workmates
from the hotel.</i>

495
00:24:21,067 --> 00:24:22,133
<i> You're dead.</i>

496
00:24:22,267 --> 00:24:23,900
<i> Looks like you're marked.</i>

497
00:24:24,033 --> 00:24:27,133
<i>It's good to hear that
you haven't forgotten me.</i>

498
00:24:27,867 --> 00:24:29,100
- [KNOCKING ON DOOR]
- [GASPS]

499
00:24:30,600 --> 00:24:32,167
<i> Is this a map of Hotel 88?</i>

500
00:24:32,300 --> 00:24:33,233
<i> But what is this?</i>

501
00:24:33,967 --> 00:24:35,767
<i>I saw a picture
among Dad's stuff.</i>

502
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:38,300
<i>I just wanted to know
if Sandro was one of them.</i>

503
00:24:38,433 --> 00:24:42,067
I need to know whether Sandro's
<i> got any family still alive.</i>

504
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:46,000
<i>You'll get dragged into this
if you don't stop, Leon.</i>
